msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../nanorc.5:32
msgid ""
"If you want the old, Pico behavior back, you can use B<set breaklonglines>, "
"B<set finalnewline>, B<set jumpyscrolling>, and B<set emptyline>."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../nanorc.5:41
msgid ""
"The I<nanorc> file contains the default settings for B<nano>, a small and "
"friendly editor.  The file should be in Unix format, not in DOS or Mac "
"format.  During startup, B<nano> will first read the system-wide settings, "
"from I</etc/nanorc> (the exact path might be different on your system), and "
"then the user-specific settings, either from I<~/.nanorc> or from I<"
"$XDG_CONFIG_HOME/nano/nanorc> or from I<~/.config/nano/nanorc>, whichever is "
"encountered first."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../nanorc.5:48
msgid ""
"The configuration file accepts a series of B<set> and B<unset> commands, "
"which can be used to configure nano on startup without using command-line "
"options.  Additionally, there are some commands to define syntax "
"highlighting and to rebind keys -- see the two separate sections on those.  "
"B<nano> reads one command per line."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../nanorc.5:55
msgid ""
"Options in I<nanorc> files take precedence over nano's defaults, and command-"
"line options override I<nanorc> settings.  Also, options that do not take an "
"argument are unset by default.  So using the B<unset> command is only needed "
"when wanting to override a setting of the system's I<nanorc> file in your "
"own I<nanorc>.  Options that take an argument cannot be unset."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../nanorc.5:61
msgid ""
"Below, the I<string> parameters need to be enclosed in double quotes.  "
"Quotes inside these string parameters don't have to be escaped with "
"backslashes.  The last double quote in the string will be treated as its "
"end.  For example, for the B<brackets> option, \"B<\"')E<gt>]}>\" will match "
"B<\">, B<'>, B<)>, B<E<gt>>, B<]>, and B<}>."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../nanorc.5:63
msgid "The supported commands and arguments are:"
msgstr ""

#. type: TP
#: ../nanorc.5:64
#, no-wrap
msgid "B<set afterends>"
msgstr ""

#. type: TP
#: ../nanorc.5:67
#, no-wrap
msgid "B<set allow_insecure_backup>"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../nanorc.5:72
msgid ""
"When backing up files, allow the backup to succeed even if its permissions "
"can't be (re)set due to special OS considerations.  You should NOT enable "
"this option unless you are sure you need it."
msgstr ""

#. type: TP
#: ../nanorc.5:72
#, no-wrap
msgid "B<set atblanks>"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../nanorc.5:76
msgid ""
"When soft line wrapping is enabled, make it wrap lines at blank characters "
"(tabs and spaces) instead of always at the edge of the screen."
msgstr ""

#. type: TP
#: ../nanorc.5:76
#, no-wrap
msgid "B<set autoindent>"
msgstr ""

#. type: TP
#: ../nanorc.5:81
#, no-wrap
msgid "B<set backup>"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../nanorc.5:85
msgid ""
"When saving a file, create a backup file by adding a tilde (B<~>) to the "
"file's name."
msgstr ""

#. type: TP
#: ../nanorc.5:85
#, no-wrap
msgid "B<set backupdir >I<directory>"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../nanorc.5:91
msgid ""
"Make and keep not just one backup file, but make and keep a uniquely "
"numbered one every time a file is saved -- when backups are enabled with "
"B<set backup> or B<--backup> or B<-B>.  The uniquely numbered files are "
"stored in the specified I<directory>."
msgstr ""

#. type: TP
#: ../nanorc.5:91
#, no-wrap
msgid "B<set boldtext>"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../nanorc.5:97
msgid ""
"Use bold instead of reverse video for the title bar, status bar, key combos, "
"function tags, line numbers, and selected text.  This can be overridden by "
"setting the options B<titlecolor>, B<statuscolor>, B<keycolor>, "
"B<functioncolor>, B<numbercolor>, and B<selectedcolor>."
msgstr ""

#. type: TP
#: ../nanorc.5:97
#, no-wrap
msgid "B<set brackets >I<string>"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../nanorc.5:103
msgid ""
"Set the characters treated as closing brackets when justifying paragraphs.  "
"This may not include blank characters.  Only closing punctuation (see B<set "
"punct>), optionally followed by the specified closing brackets, can end "
"sentences.  The default value is \"B<\"')E<gt>]}>\"."
msgstr ""

#. type: TP
#: ../nanorc.5:103
#, no-wrap
msgid "B<set breaklonglines>"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../nanorc.5:106
msgid "Automatically hard-wrap the current line when it becomes overlong."
msgstr ""

#. type: TP
#: ../nanorc.5:106
#, no-wrap
msgid "B<set casesensitive>"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../nanorc.5:109
msgid "Do case-sensitive searches by default."
msgstr ""

#. type: TP
#: ../nanorc.5:109
#, no-wrap
msgid "B<set constantshow>"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../nanorc.5:113
msgid ""
"Constantly display the cursor position in the status bar.  This overrides "
"the option B<quickblank>."
msgstr ""

#. type: TP
#: ../nanorc.5:113
#, no-wrap
msgid "B<set cutfromcursor>"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../nanorc.5:116
msgid ""
"Use cut-from-cursor-to-end-of-line by default, instead of cutting the whole "
"line."
msgstr ""

#. type: TP
#: ../nanorc.5:116
#, no-wrap
msgid "B<set emptyline>"
msgstr ""

#. type: TP
#: ../nanorc.5:119
#, no-wrap
msgid "B<set errorcolor >I<fgcolor>,I<bgcolor>"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../nanorc.5:123
msgid ""
"Use this color combination for the status bar when an error message is "
"displayed.  See B<set titlecolor> for valid color names."
msgstr ""

#. type: TP
#: ../nanorc.5:123
#, no-wrap
msgid "B<set finalnewline>"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../nanorc.5:126
msgid ""
"If the buffer is not empty, ensure that it ends with a newline character."
msgstr ""

#. type: TP
#: ../nanorc.5:126
#, no-wrap
msgid "B<set fill >I<number>"
msgstr ""

#. type: TP
#: ../nanorc.5:133
#, no-wrap
msgid "B<set functioncolor >I<fgcolor>,I<bgcolor>"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../nanorc.5:138
msgid ""
"Specify the color combination to use for the function descriptions in the "
"two help lines at the bottom of the screen.  See B<set titlecolor> for more "
"details."
msgstr ""

#. type: TP
#: ../nanorc.5:138
#, no-wrap
msgid "B<set historylog>"
msgstr ""

#. type: TP
#: ../nanorc.5:142
#, no-wrap
msgid "B<set jumpyscrolling>"
msgstr ""

#. type: TP
#: ../nanorc.5:145
#, no-wrap
msgid "B<set keycolor >I<fgcolor>,I<bgcolor>"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../nanorc.5:150
msgid ""
"Specify the color combination to use for the shortcut key combos in the two "
"help lines at the bottom of the screen.  See B<set titlecolor> for more "
"details."
msgstr ""

#. type: TP
#: ../nanorc.5:150
#, no-wrap
msgid "B<set linenumbers>"
msgstr ""

#. type: TP
#: ../nanorc.5:153
#, no-wrap
msgid "B<set locking>"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../nanorc.5:156
msgid "Enable vim-style lock-files for when editing files."
msgstr ""

#. type: TP
#: ../nanorc.5:156
#, no-wrap
msgid "B<set guidestripe >I<number>"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../nanorc.5:160
msgid ""
"Draw a vertical stripe at the given column, to help judge the width of the "
"text.  (The color of the stripe can be changed with B<set stripecolor>.)"
msgstr ""

#. type: TP
#: ../nanorc.5:160
#, no-wrap
msgid "B<set matchbrackets >I<string>"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../nanorc.5:166
msgid ""
"Set the opening and closing brackets that can be found by bracket searches.  "
"This may not include blank characters.  The opening set must come before the "
"closing set, and the two sets must be in the same order.  The default value "
"is \"B<(E<lt>[{)E<gt>]}>\"."
msgstr ""

#. type: TP
#: ../nanorc.5:166
#, no-wrap
msgid "B<set morespace>"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../nanorc.5:170
msgid ""
"Deprecated option since it has become the default setting.  When needed, use "
"B<unset emptyline> instead."
msgstr ""

#. type: TP
#: ../nanorc.5:170
#, no-wrap
msgid "B<set mouse>"
msgstr ""

#. type: TP
#: ../nanorc.5:177
#, no-wrap
msgid "B<set multibuffer>"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../nanorc.5:180
msgid "When reading in a file with ^R, insert it into a new buffer by default."
msgstr ""

#. type: TP
#: ../nanorc.5:180
#, no-wrap
msgid "B<set noconvert>"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../nanorc.5:183
msgid "Don't convert files from DOS/Mac format."
msgstr ""

#. type: TP
#: ../nanorc.5:183
#, no-wrap
msgid "B<set nohelp>"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../nanorc.5:186
msgid "Don't display the two help lines at the bottom of the screen."
msgstr ""

#. type: TP
#: ../nanorc.5:186
#, no-wrap
msgid "B<set nonewlines>"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../nanorc.5:190
msgid ""
"Deprecated option since it has become the default setting.  When needed, use "
"B<unset finalnewline> instead."
msgstr ""

#. type: TP
#: ../nanorc.5:190
#, no-wrap
msgid "B<set nopauses>"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../nanorc.5:194
msgid ""
"Don't pause between warnings at startup.  This means that only the last one "
"will be visible (when there are multiple ones)."
msgstr ""

#. type: TP
#: ../nanorc.5:194
#, no-wrap
msgid "B<set nowrap>"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../nanorc.5:198
msgid ""
"Deprecated option since it has become the default setting.  When needed, use "
"B<unset breaklonglines> instead."
msgstr ""

#. type: TP
#: ../nanorc.5:198
#, no-wrap
msgid "B<set numbercolor >I<fgcolor>,I<bgcolor>"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../nanorc.5:202
msgid ""
"Specify the color combination to use for line numbers.  See B<set "
"titlecolor> for more details."
msgstr ""

#. type: TP
#: ../nanorc.5:202
#, no-wrap
msgid "B<set operatingdir >I<directory>"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../nanorc.5:208
msgid ""
"B<nano> will only read and write files inside I<directory> and its "
"subdirectories.  Also, the current directory is changed to here, so files "
"are inserted from this directory.  By default, the operating directory "
"feature is turned off."
msgstr ""

#. type: TP
#: ../nanorc.5:208
#, no-wrap
msgid "B<set positionlog>"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../nanorc.5:212
msgid ""
"Save the cursor position of files between editing sessions.  The cursor "
"position is remembered for the 200 most-recently edited files."
msgstr ""

#. type: TP
#: ../nanorc.5:212
#, no-wrap
msgid "B<set preserve>"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../nanorc.5:215
msgid "Preserve the XON and XOFF keys (^Q and ^S)."
msgstr ""

#. type: TP
#: ../nanorc.5:215
#, no-wrap
msgid "B<set punct >I<string>"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../nanorc.5:221
msgid ""
"Set the characters treated as closing punctuation when justifying "
"paragraphs.  This may not include blank characters.  Only the specfified "
"closing punctuation, optionally followed by closing brackets (see "
"B<brackets>), can end sentences.  The default value is \"B<!.?>\"."
msgstr ""

#. type: TP
#: ../nanorc.5:221
#, no-wrap
msgid "B<set quickblank>"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../nanorc.5:225
msgid ""
"Do quick status-bar blanking: status-bar messages will disappear after 1 "
"keystroke instead of 25.  The option B<constantshow> overrides this."
msgstr ""

#. type: TP
#: ../nanorc.5:225
#, no-wrap
msgid "B<set quotestr >I<regex>"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../nanorc.5:232
msgid ""
"Set the regular expression for matching the quoting part of a line.  The "
"default value is \"B<^([\\ \\et]*([!#%:;E<gt>|}]|//|--))+>\".  (Note that B<"
"\\et> stands for an actual Tab character.)  This makes it possible to "
"rejustify blocks of quoted text when composing email, and to rewrap blocks "
"of line comments when writing source code."
msgstr ""

#. type: TP
#: ../nanorc.5:232
#, no-wrap
msgid "B<set rawsequences>"
msgstr ""

#. type: TP
#: ../nanorc.5:238
#, no-wrap
msgid "B<set rebinddelete>"
msgstr ""

#. type: TP
#: ../nanorc.5:243
#, no-wrap
msgid "B<set regexp>"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../nanorc.5:246
msgid "Do extended regular expression searches by default."
msgstr ""

#. type: TP
#: ../nanorc.5:246
#, no-wrap
msgid "B<set selectedcolor >I<fgcolor>,I<bgcolor>"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../nanorc.5:250
msgid ""
"Specify the color combination to use for selected text.  See B<set "
"titlecolor> for more details."
msgstr ""

#. type: TP
#: ../nanorc.5:250
#, no-wrap
msgid "B<set showcursor>"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../nanorc.5:254
msgid ""
"Put the cursor on the highlighted item in the file browser, to aid braille "
"users."
msgstr ""

#. type: TP
#: ../nanorc.5:254
#, no-wrap
msgid "B<set smarthome>"
msgstr ""

#. type: TP
#: ../nanorc.5:261
#, no-wrap
msgid "B<set smooth>"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../nanorc.5:265
msgid ""
"Deprecated option since it has become the default setting.  When needed, use "
"B<unset jumpyscrolling> instead."
msgstr ""

#. type: TP
#: ../nanorc.5:265
#, no-wrap
msgid "B<set softwrap>"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../nanorc.5:268
msgid "Enable soft line wrapping for easier viewing of very long lines."
msgstr ""

#. type: TP
#: ../nanorc.5:268
#, no-wrap
msgid "B<set speller >I<program>"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../nanorc.5:272
msgid ""
"Use the given I<program> to do spell checking and correcting, instead of the "
"built-in corrector that calls B<spell>."
msgstr ""

#. type: TP
#: ../nanorc.5:272
#, no-wrap
msgid "B<set statuscolor >I<fgcolor>,I<bgcolor>"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../nanorc.5:276
msgid ""
"Specify the color combination to use for the status bar.  See B<set "
"titlecolor> for more details."
msgstr ""

#. type: TP
#: ../nanorc.5:276
#, no-wrap
msgid "B<set stripecolor >I<fgcolor>,I<bgcolor>"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../nanorc.5:280
msgid ""
"Specify the color combination to use for the vertical guiding stripe.  See "
"B<set titlecolor> for more details."
msgstr ""

#. type: TP
#: ../nanorc.5:280
#, no-wrap
msgid "B<set suspend>"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../nanorc.5:283
msgid "Allow B<nano> to be suspended."
msgstr ""

#. type: TP
#: ../nanorc.5:283
#, no-wrap
msgid "B<set tabsize >I<number>"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../nanorc.5:287
msgid ""
"Use a tab size of I<number> columns.  The value of I<number> must be greater "
"than 0.  The default value is B<8>."
msgstr ""

#. type: TP
#: ../nanorc.5:287
#, no-wrap
msgid "B<set tabstospaces>"
msgstr ""

#. type: TP
#: ../nanorc.5:290
#, no-wrap
msgid "B<set tempfile>"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../nanorc.5:293
msgid "Save automatically on exit, don't prompt."
msgstr ""

#. type: TP
#: ../nanorc.5:293
#, no-wrap
msgid "B<set titlecolor >I<fgcolor>,I<bgcolor>"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../nanorc.5:302
msgid ""
"Specify the color combination to use for the title bar.  Valid names for the "
"foreground and background colors are: B<white>, B<black>, B<blue>, B<green>, "
"B<red>, B<cyan>, B<yellow>, B<magenta>, and B<normal> -- where B<normal> "
"means the default foreground or background color.  The name of the "
"foreground color may be prefixed with B<bright>.  And either \"I<fgcolor>\" "
"or \",I<bgcolor>\" may be left out."
msgstr ""

#. type: TP
#: ../nanorc.5:302
#, no-wrap
msgid "B<set trimblanks>"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../nanorc.5:306
msgid ""
"Remove trailing whitespace from wrapped lines when automatic hard-wrapping "
"occurs or when text is justified."
msgstr ""

#. type: TP
#: ../nanorc.5:306
#, no-wrap
msgid "B<set unix>"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../nanorc.5:311
msgid ""
"Save a file by default in Unix format.  This overrides nano's default "
"behavior of saving a file in the format that it had.  (This option has no "
"effect when you also use B<set noconvert>.)"
msgstr ""

#. type: TP
#: ../nanorc.5:311
#, no-wrap
msgid "B<set view>"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../nanorc.5:316
msgid ""
"Disallow file modification: read-only mode.  This mode allows the user to "
"open also other files for viewing, unless B<--restricted> is given on the "
"command line."
msgstr ""

#. type: TP
#: ../nanorc.5:316
#, no-wrap
msgid "B<set whitespace >I<string>"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../nanorc.5:321
msgid ""
"Set the two characters used to indicate the presence of tabs and spaces.  "
"They must be single-column characters.  The default pair for a UTF-8 locale "
"is \"B<\\[Fc]\\[md]>\", and for other locales \"B<E<gt>.>\"."
msgstr ""

#. type: TP
#: ../nanorc.5:321
#, no-wrap
msgid "B<set wordbounds>"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../nanorc.5:325
msgid ""
"Detect word boundaries differently by treating punctuation characters as "
"parts of words."
msgstr ""

#. type: TP
#: ../nanorc.5:325
#, no-wrap
msgid "B<set wordchars >I<string>"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../nanorc.5:330
msgid ""
"Specify which other characters (besides the normal alphanumeric ones)  "
"should be considered as parts of words.  This overrides the option "
"B<wordbounds>."
msgstr ""

#. type: TP
#: ../nanorc.5:330
#, no-wrap
msgid "B<set zap>"
msgstr ""

#. type: SH
#: ../nanorc.5:335
#, no-wrap
msgid "SYNTAX HIGHLIGHTING"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../nanorc.5:342
msgid ""
"Coloring the different syntactic elements of a file is done via regular "
"expressions (see the B<color> command below).  This is inherently imperfect, "
"because regular expressions are not powerful enough to fully parse a file.  "
"Nevertheless, regular expressions can do a lot and are easy to make, so they "
"are a good fit for a small editor like B<nano>."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../nanorc.5:345
msgid ""
"For each kind of file a separate syntax can be defined via the following "
"commands:"
msgstr ""

#. type: TP
#: ../nanorc.5:345
#, no-wrap
msgid "B<syntax>I< name >[B<\">I<fileregex>B<\" >...]"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../nanorc.5:351
msgid ""
"Start the definition of a syntax with this I<name>.  All subsequent B<color> "
"and other such commands will be added to this syntax, until a new B<syntax> "
"command is encountered."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../nanorc.5:357
msgid ""
"When B<nano> is run, this syntax will be automatically activated if the "
"current filename matches the extended regular expression I<fileregex>.  Or "
"the syntax can be explicitly activated by using the B<-Y> or B<--syntax> "
"command-line option followed by the I<name>."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../nanorc.5:362
msgid ""
"The syntax B<default> is special: it takes no I<fileregex>, and applies to "
"files that don't match any syntax's regexes.  The syntax B<none> is "
"reserved; specifying it on the command line is the same as not having a "
"syntax at all."
msgstr ""

#. type: TP
#: ../nanorc.5:362
#, no-wrap
msgid "B<header \">I<regex>B<\" >..."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../nanorc.5:367
msgid ""
"If from all defined syntaxes no I<fileregex> matched, then compare this "
"I<regex> (or regexes) against the first line of the current file, to "
"determine whether this syntax should be used for it."
msgstr ""

#. type: TP
#: ../nanorc.5:367
#, no-wrap
msgid "B<magic \">I<regex>B<\" >..."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../nanorc.5:375
msgid ""
"If no I<fileregex> matched and no B<header> regex matched either, then "
"compare this I<regex> (or regexes) against the result of querying the "
"B<magic> database about the current file, to determine whether this syntax "
"should be used for it.  (This functionality only works when B<libmagic> is "
"installed on the system and will be silently ignored otherwise.)"
msgstr ""

#. type: TP
#: ../nanorc.5:375
#, no-wrap
msgid "B<linter>I< program >[I<arg >...]"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../nanorc.5:378
msgid "Use the given I<program> to run a syntax check on the current buffer."
msgstr ""

#. type: TP
#: ../nanorc.5:378
#, no-wrap
msgid "B<comment \">I<string>B<\">"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../nanorc.5:389
msgid ""
"Use the given I<string> for commenting and uncommenting lines.  If the "
"string contains a vertical bar or pipe character (B<|>), this designates "
"bracket-style comments; for example, \"B</*|*/>\" for CSS files.  The "
"characters before the pipe are prepended to the line and the characters "
"after the pipe are appended at the end of the line.  If no pipe character is "
"present, the full string is prepended; for example, \"B<#>\" for Python "
"files.  If empty double quotes are specified, the comment/uncomment function "
"is disabled; for example, \"\" for JSON.  The default value is \"B<#>\"."
msgstr ""

#. type: TP
#: ../nanorc.5:389
#, no-wrap
msgid "B<color >I<fgcolor>B<,>I<bgcolor>B< \">I<regex>B<\" >..."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../nanorc.5:402
msgid ""
"Display all pieces of text that match the extended regular expression "
"I<regex> with foreground color I<fgcolor> and background color I<bgcolor>, "
"at least one of which must be specified.  Valid names for foreground and "
"background colors are: B<white>, B<black>, B<blue>, B<green>, B<red>, "
"B<cyan>, B<yellow>, B<magenta>, and B<normal> -- where B<normal> means the "
"default foreground or background color.  You may use the prefix B<bright> to "
"get a stronger color highlight for the foreground.  If your terminal "
"supports transparency, not specifying a I<bgcolor> tells B<nano> to attempt "
"to use a transparent background."
msgstr ""

#. type: TP
#: ../nanorc.5:402
#, no-wrap
msgid "B<icolor >I<fgcolor>B<,>I<bgcolor>B< \">I<regex>B<\" >..."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../nanorc.5:405 ../nanorc.5:417
msgid "Same as above, except that the matching is case insensitive."
msgstr ""

#. type: TP
#: ../nanorc.5:405
#, no-wrap
msgid "B<color >I<fgcolor>B<,>I<bgcolor>B< start=\">I<fromrx>B<\" end=\">I<torx>B<\">"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../nanorc.5:414
msgid ""
"Display all pieces of text whose start matches extended regular expression "
"I<fromrx> and whose end matches extended regular expression I<torx> with "
"foreground color I<fgcolor> and background color I<bgcolor>, at least one of "
"which must be specified.  This means that, after an initial instance of "
"I<fromrx>, all text until the first instance of I<torx> will be colored.  "
"This allows syntax highlighting to span multiple lines."
msgstr ""

#. type: TP
#: ../nanorc.5:414
#, no-wrap
msgid "B<icolor >I<fgcolor>B<,>I<bgcolor>B< start=\">I<fromrx>B<\" end=\">I<torx>B<\">"
msgstr ""

#. type: TP
#: ../nanorc.5:417
#, no-wrap
msgid "B<include \">I<syntaxfile>B<\">"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../nanorc.5:422
msgid ""
"Read in self-contained color syntaxes from I<syntaxfile>.  Note that "
"I<syntaxfile> may contain only the above commands, from B<syntax> to "
"B<icolor>."
msgstr ""

#. type: TP
#: ../nanorc.5:422
#, no-wrap
msgid "B<extendsyntax>I< name command >[I<arg >...]"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../nanorc.5:430
msgid ""
"Extend the syntax previously defined as I<name> with another I<command>.  "
"This allows adding a new B<color>, B<icolor>, B<header>, B<magic>, "
"B<comment>, or B<linter> command to an already defined syntax -- useful when "
"you want to slightly improve a syntax defined in one of the system-installed "
"files (which normally are not writable)."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../nanorc.5:437
msgid ""
"Note: the B<formatter> command has been removed.  It was superseded by a "
"more general mechanism: the filtering of buffer or marked text through an "
"external command.  Such filtering is done by typing B<^R^X> and then "
"preceding your formatter command with the pipe symbol (B<|>).  It has the "
"added advantage that the operation can be undone."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../nanorc.5:440
msgid ""
"If you use such a formatting command regularly, you could assign the "
"relevant series of keystrokes to a single key in your nanorc:"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../nanorc.5:443
msgid "B<bind M-F \"^R^X|yourformatcommand^M\" main>"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../nanorc.5:447
msgid ""
"(Note that the B<^R>, B<^X>, and B<^M> are each a single, literal control "
"character.  You can enter them by preceding each with B<M-V>.)"
msgstr ""

#. type: SH
#: ../nanorc.5:448
#, no-wrap
msgid "REBINDING KEYS"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../nanorc.5:450
msgid "Key bindings can be changed via the following three commands:"
msgstr ""

#. type: TP
#: ../nanorc.5:451
#, no-wrap
msgid "B<bind>I< key function menu>"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../nanorc.5:456
msgid ""
"Rebinds the key I<key> to a new function named I<function> in the context of "
"menu I<menu> (or in all menus where the function exists by using B<all>)."
msgstr ""

#. type: TP
#: ../nanorc.5:456
#, no-wrap
msgid "B<bind>I< key >B<\">I<string>B<\">I< menu>"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../nanorc.5:463
msgid ""
"Makes the given I<key> produce the given I<string> in the given I<menu> (or "
"in all menus where the key exists when B<all> is used).  The I<string> can "
"consist of text or commands or a mix of them.  (To enter a command into the "
"I<string>, precede its keystroke with B<M-V>.)"
msgstr ""

#. type: TP
#: ../nanorc.5:464
#, no-wrap
msgid "B<unbind>I< key menu>"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../nanorc.5:468
msgid ""
"Unbinds the key I<key> from the menu named I<menu> (or from all menus where "
"it exists by using B<all>)."
msgstr ""

#. type: TP
#: ../nanorc.5:470
#, no-wrap
msgid "The format of I<key> should be one of:"
msgstr ""

#. type: TP
#: ../nanorc.5:473
#, no-wrap
msgid "B<^>"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../nanorc.5:478
msgid ""
"followed by a Latin letter, by one of several ASCII characters (@, ], \\e, "
"^, or _), or by the word \"Space\".  Example: ^C."
msgstr ""

#. type: TP
#: ../nanorc.5:478
#, no-wrap
msgid "B<M->"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../nanorc.5:482
msgid ""
"followed by any ASCII character except [, or by the word \"Space\".  "
"Example: M-C."
msgstr ""

#. type: TP
#: ../nanorc.5:482
#, no-wrap
msgid "B<F>"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../nanorc.5:486
msgid "followed by a numeric value from 1 to 16.  Example: F10."
msgstr ""

#. type: TP
#: ../nanorc.5:486
#, no-wrap
msgid "the word \"Ins\" or the word \"Del\"."
msgstr ""

#. type: TP
#: ../nanorc.5:490
#, no-wrap
msgid "Valid I<function> names to be bound are:"
msgstr ""

#. type: TP
#: ../nanorc.5:493 ../nanorc.5:849
#, no-wrap
msgid "B<help>"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../nanorc.5:496
msgid "Invokes the help viewer."
msgstr ""

#. type: TP
#: ../nanorc.5:496
#, no-wrap
msgid "B<cancel>"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../nanorc.5:499
msgid "Cancels the current command."
msgstr ""

#. type: TP
#: ../nanorc.5:499
#, no-wrap
msgid "B<exit>"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../nanorc.5:502
msgid "Exits from the program (or from the help viewer or the file browser)."
msgstr ""

#. type: TP
#: ../nanorc.5:502 ../nanorc.5:840
#, no-wrap
msgid "B<writeout>"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../nanorc.5:505
msgid "Writes the current buffer to disk, asking for a name."
msgstr ""

#. type: TP
#: ../nanorc.5:505
#, no-wrap
msgid "B<savefile>"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../nanorc.5:508
msgid "Writes the current file to disk without prompting."
msgstr ""

#. type: TP
#: ../nanorc.5:508 ../nanorc.5:843
#, no-wrap
msgid "B<insert>"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../nanorc.5:512
msgid ""
"Inserts a file into the current buffer (at the current cursor position), or "
"into a new buffer when option B<multibuffer> is set."
msgstr ""

#. type: TP
#: ../nanorc.5:512
#, no-wrap
msgid "B<whereis>"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../nanorc.5:516
msgid ""
"Starts a forward search for text in the current buffer -- or for filenames "
"matching a string in the current list in the file browser."
msgstr ""

#. type: TP
#: ../nanorc.5:516
#, no-wrap
msgid "B<wherewas>"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../nanorc.5:520
msgid ""
"Starts a backward search for text in the current buffer -- or for filenames "
"matching a string in the current list in the file browser."
msgstr ""

#. type: TP
#: ../nanorc.5:520
#, no-wrap
msgid "B<findprevious>"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../nanorc.5:523
msgid "Searches the next occurrence in the backward direction."
msgstr ""

#. type: TP
#: ../nanorc.5:523
#, no-wrap
msgid "B<findnext>"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../nanorc.5:526
msgid "Searches the next occurrence in the forward direction."
msgstr ""

#. type: TP
#: ../nanorc.5:526 ../nanorc.5:828
#, no-wrap
msgid "B<replace>"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../nanorc.5:529
msgid "Interactively replaces text within the current buffer."
msgstr ""

#. type: TP
#: ../nanorc.5:529
#, no-wrap
msgid "B<cut>"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../nanorc.5:532
msgid "Cuts and stores the current line (or the marked region)."
msgstr ""

#. type: TP
#: ../nanorc.5:532
#, no-wrap
msgid "B<copy>"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../nanorc.5:535
msgid "Copies the current line (or the marked region) without deleting it."
msgstr ""

#. type: TP
#: ../nanorc.5:535
#, no-wrap
msgid "B<paste>"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../nanorc.5:539
msgid ""
"Pastes the currently stored text into the current buffer at the current "
"cursor position."
msgstr ""

#. type: TP
#: ../nanorc.5:539
#, no-wrap
msgid "B<zap>"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../nanorc.5:543
msgid ""
"Throws away the current line (or the marked region).  (This function is "
"bound by default to E<lt>Meta+DeleteE<gt>.)"
msgstr ""

#. type: TP
#: ../nanorc.5:543
#, no-wrap
msgid "B<chopwordleft>"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../nanorc.5:549
msgid ""
"Deletes from the cursor position to the beginning of the preceding word.  "
"(This function is bound by default to E<lt>Shift+Ctrl+DeleteE<gt>.  If your "
"terminal produces B<^H> for E<lt>Ctrl+BackspaceE<gt>, you can make E<lt>Ctrl"
"+BackspaceE<gt> delete the word to the left of the cursor by rebinding ^H to "
"this function.)"
msgstr ""

#. type: TP
#: ../nanorc.5:549
#, no-wrap
msgid "B<chopwordright>"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../nanorc.5:553
msgid ""
"Deletes from the cursor position to the beginning of the next word.  (This "
"function is bound by default to E<lt>Ctrl+DeleteE<gt>.)"
msgstr ""

#. type: TP
#: ../nanorc.5:553
#, no-wrap
msgid "B<cutrestoffile>"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../nanorc.5:556
msgid "Cuts all text from the cursor position till the end of the buffer."
msgstr ""

#. type: TP
#: ../nanorc.5:556
#, no-wrap
msgid "B<mark>"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../nanorc.5:560
msgid ""
"Sets the mark at the current position, to start selecting text.  Or, when it "
"is set, unsets the mark."
msgstr ""

#. type: TP
#: ../nanorc.5:560
#, no-wrap
msgid "B<curpos>"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../nanorc.5:563
msgid ""
"Shows the current cursor position: the line, column, and character positions."
msgstr ""

#. type: TP
#: ../nanorc.5:563
#, no-wrap
msgid "B<wordcount>"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../nanorc.5:566
msgid "Counts the number of words, lines and characters in the current buffer."
msgstr ""

#. type: TP
#: ../nanorc.5:566
#, no-wrap
msgid "B<speller>"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../nanorc.5:570
msgid ""
"Invokes a spell-checking program, either the default one, or the one defined "
"by B<--speller> or B<set speller>."
msgstr ""

#. type: TP
#: ../nanorc.5:570 ../nanorc.5:855
#, no-wrap
msgid "B<linter>"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../nanorc.5:573
msgid "Invokes a syntax-checking program (if the active syntax defines one)."
msgstr ""

#. type: TP
#: ../nanorc.5:573
#, no-wrap
msgid "B<justify>"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../nanorc.5:579
msgid ""
"Justifies the current paragraph.  A paragraph is a group of contiguous lines "
"that, apart from possibly the first line, all have the same indentation.  "
"The beginning of a paragraph is detected by either this lone line with a "
"differing indentation or by a preceding blank line."
msgstr ""

#. type: TP
#: ../nanorc.5:579
#, no-wrap
msgid "B<fulljustify>"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../nanorc.5:582
msgid "Justifies the entire current buffer."
msgstr ""

#. type: TP
#: ../nanorc.5:582
#, no-wrap
msgid "B<indent>"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../nanorc.5:585
msgid "Indents (shifts to the right) the currently marked text."
msgstr ""

#. type: TP
#: ../nanorc.5:585
#, no-wrap
msgid "B<unindent>"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../nanorc.5:588
msgid "Unindents (shifts to the left) the currently marked text."
msgstr ""

#. type: TP
#: ../nanorc.5:588
#, no-wrap
msgid "B<comment>"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../nanorc.5:592
msgid ""
"Comments or uncomments the current line or marked lines, using the comment "
"style specified in the active syntax."
msgstr ""

#. type: TP
#: ../nanorc.5:592
#, no-wrap
msgid "B<complete>"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../nanorc.5:596
msgid ""
"Completes the fragment before the cursor to a full word found elsewhere in "
"the current buffer."
msgstr ""

#. type: TP
#: ../nanorc.5:596
#, no-wrap
msgid "B<left>"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../nanorc.5:599
msgid "Goes left one position (in the editor or browser)."
msgstr ""

#. type: TP
#: ../nanorc.5:599
#, no-wrap
msgid "B<right>"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../nanorc.5:602
msgid "Goes right one position (in the editor or browser)."
msgstr ""

#. type: TP
#: ../nanorc.5:602
#, no-wrap
msgid "B<up>"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../nanorc.5:605
msgid "Goes one line up (in the editor or browser)."
msgstr ""

#. type: TP
#: ../nanorc.5:605
#, no-wrap
msgid "B<down>"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../nanorc.5:608
msgid "Goes one line down (in the editor or browser)."
msgstr ""

#. type: TP
#: ../nanorc.5:608
#, no-wrap
msgid "B<scrollup>"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../nanorc.5:612
msgid ""
"Scrolls the viewport up one row (meaning that the text slides down)  while "
"keeping the cursor in the same text position, if possible."
msgstr ""

#. type: TP
#: ../nanorc.5:612
#, no-wrap
msgid "B<scrolldown>"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../nanorc.5:616
msgid ""
"Scrolls the viewport down one row (meaning that the text slides up)  while "
"keeping the cursor in the same text position, if possible."
msgstr ""

#. type: TP
#: ../nanorc.5:616
#, no-wrap
msgid "B<prevword>"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../nanorc.5:619
msgid "Moves the cursor to the beginning of the previous word."
msgstr ""

#. type: TP
#: ../nanorc.5:619
#, no-wrap
msgid "B<nextword>"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../nanorc.5:622
msgid "Moves the cursor to the beginning of the next word."
msgstr ""

#. type: TP
#: ../nanorc.5:622
#, no-wrap
msgid "B<home>"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../nanorc.5:625
msgid "Moves the cursor to the beginning of the current line."
msgstr ""

#. type: TP
#: ../nanorc.5:625
#, no-wrap
msgid "B<end>"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../nanorc.5:628
msgid "Moves the cursor to the end of the current line."
msgstr ""

#. type: TP
#: ../nanorc.5:628
#, no-wrap
msgid "B<beginpara>"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../nanorc.5:631
msgid "Moves the cursor to the beginning of the current paragraph."
msgstr ""

#. type: TP
#: ../nanorc.5:631
#, no-wrap
msgid "B<endpara>"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../nanorc.5:634
msgid "Moves the cursor to the end of the current paragraph."
msgstr ""

#. type: TP
#: ../nanorc.5:634
#, no-wrap
msgid "B<prevblock>"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../nanorc.5:638
msgid ""
"Moves the cursor to the beginning of the current or preceding block of "
"text.  (Blocks are separated by one or more blank lines.)"
msgstr ""

#. type: TP
#: ../nanorc.5:638
#, no-wrap
msgid "B<nextblock>"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../nanorc.5:641
msgid "Moves the cursor to the beginning of the next block of text."
msgstr ""

#. type: TP
#: ../nanorc.5:641
#, no-wrap
msgid "B<pageup>"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../nanorc.5:644
msgid "Goes up one screenful."
msgstr ""

#. type: TP
#: ../nanorc.5:644
#, no-wrap
msgid "B<pagedown>"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../nanorc.5:647
msgid "Goes down one screenful."
msgstr ""

#. type: TP
#: ../nanorc.5:647
#, no-wrap
msgid "B<firstline>"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../nanorc.5:650
msgid "Goes to the first line of the file."
msgstr ""

#. type: TP
#: ../nanorc.5:650
#, no-wrap
msgid "B<lastline>"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../nanorc.5:653
msgid "Goes to the last line of the file."
msgstr ""

#. type: TP
#: ../nanorc.5:653 ../nanorc.5:837
#, no-wrap
msgid "B<gotoline>"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../nanorc.5:657
msgid ""
"Goes to a specific line (and column if specified).  Negative numbers count "
"from the end of the file (and end of the line)."
msgstr ""

#. type: TP
#: ../nanorc.5:657
#, no-wrap
msgid "B<findbracket>"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../nanorc.5:661
msgid ""
"Moves the cursor to the bracket (brace, parenthesis, etc.) that matches "
"(pairs) with the one under the cursor."
msgstr ""

#. type: TP
#: ../nanorc.5:661
#, no-wrap
msgid "B<prevbuf>"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../nanorc.5:664
msgid ""
"Switches to editing/viewing the previous buffer when multiple buffers are "
"open."
msgstr ""

#. type: TP
#: ../nanorc.5:664
#, no-wrap
msgid "B<nextbuf>"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../nanorc.5:667
msgid ""
"Switches to editing/viewing the next buffer when multiple buffers are open."
msgstr ""

#. type: TP
#: ../nanorc.5:667
#, no-wrap
msgid "B<verbatim>"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../nanorc.5:670
msgid "Inserts the next keystroke verbatim into the file."
msgstr ""

#. type: TP
#: ../nanorc.5:670
#, no-wrap
msgid "B<tab>"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../nanorc.5:673
msgid "Inserts a tab at the current cursor location."
msgstr ""

#. type: TP
#: ../nanorc.5:673
#, no-wrap
msgid "B<enter>"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../nanorc.5:676
msgid "Inserts a new line below the current one."
msgstr ""

#. type: TP
#: ../nanorc.5:676
#, no-wrap
msgid "B<delete>"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../nanorc.5:679
msgid "Deletes the character under the cursor."
msgstr ""

#. type: TP
#: ../nanorc.5:679
#, no-wrap
msgid "B<backspace>"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../nanorc.5:682
msgid "Deletes the character before the cursor."
msgstr ""

#. type: TP
#: ../nanorc.5:682
#, no-wrap
msgid "B<recordmacro>"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../nanorc.5:686
msgid ""
"Starts the recording of keystrokes -- the keystrokes are stored as a macro.  "
"When already recording, the recording is stopped."
msgstr ""

#. type: TP
#: ../nanorc.5:686
#, no-wrap
msgid "B<runmacro>"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../nanorc.5:689
msgid "Replays the keystrokes of the last recorded macro."
msgstr ""

#. type: TP
#: ../nanorc.5:689
#, no-wrap
msgid "B<undo>"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../nanorc.5:692
msgid "Undoes the last performed text action (add text, delete text, etc)."
msgstr ""

#. type: TP
#: ../nanorc.5:692
#, no-wrap
msgid "B<redo>"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../nanorc.5:695
msgid "Redoes the last undone action (i.e., it undoes an undo)."
msgstr ""

#. type: TP
#: ../nanorc.5:695
#, no-wrap
msgid "B<refresh>"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../nanorc.5:698
msgid "Refreshes the screen."
msgstr ""

#. type: TP
#: ../nanorc.5:698
#, no-wrap
msgid "B<suspend>"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../nanorc.5:702
msgid ""
"Suspends the editor (if the suspending function is enabled, see the "
"\"suspendenable\" entry below)."
msgstr ""

#. type: TP
#: ../nanorc.5:702
#, no-wrap
msgid "B<casesens>"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../nanorc.5:706
msgid ""
"Toggles whether searching/replacing ignores or respects the case of the "
"given characters."
msgstr ""

#. type: TP
#: ../nanorc.5:706
#, no-wrap
msgid "B<regexp>"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../nanorc.5:709
msgid ""
"Toggles whether searching/replacing uses literal strings or regular "
"expressions."
msgstr ""

#. type: TP
#: ../nanorc.5:709
#, no-wrap
msgid "B<backwards>"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../nanorc.5:712
msgid "Toggles whether searching/replacing goes forward or backward."
msgstr ""

#. type: TP
#: ../nanorc.5:712
#, no-wrap
msgid "B<older>"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../nanorc.5:715
msgid "Retrieves the previous (earlier) entry at a prompt."
msgstr ""

#. type: TP
#: ../nanorc.5:715
#, no-wrap
msgid "B<newer>"
